<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-02-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-02-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="957" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d957">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Woodford</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-02-09"><hi rend="italic">February 9,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>There has appeared in the public prints a letter, addressed early in
                            December last by the Spanish minister to Mr. Canalejas, and which the
                            minister admits was written by him. It contains expressions concerning
                            the President of the United States of such character as to end the
                            minister’s utility as a medium for frank and sincere intercourse between
                            this country and Spain. You are, therefore, instructed to at once say to
                            the minister of state that the immediate recall of the minister is
                            expected by the President.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Day</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting.</hi></signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>